author: Steve Peloquin
title: LSWA Polls Following Week 7 Games
text:
LSWA Polls Following Week 7 Games By Steve Peloquin October 20, 2015 6:57 AM (Photo by Christian Petersen/Getty Images) 

The eighth LSWA set of high school football rankings for 2015, and seventh during the regular season, were released on Monday, with nine teams representing the Acadiana area ranked in the respective polls. 
In Class 4A, Crowley is ranked second, followed by St. Thomas More, who is third, and Teurlings Catholic, who checks in at number four. 
In the Class 3A poll, Church Point is number five this week, while Eunice comes in at number seven. 
Moving on to the Class 2A poll, Notre Dame is ranked at the very top of the poll. 
Finally, in Class 1A, Ascension Episcopal is ranked second, while Vermilion Catholic checks in at number six, with Hamilton Christian coming in at number eight. 
Below are the complete polls, including records, number of first-place votes received, and total points:

1. Rummel (5) 6-1 98 2. West Monroe (4) 7-0 94 3. Destrehan 7-0 85 4. John Curtis 5-1 79 5. Airline 5-1 67 6. Brother Martin 6-1 59 7. Zachary 6-1 42 9. Parkway 6-1 40 10. Byrd 6-1 22
